Before starting any new project or implementing a new feature, ALWAYS run `/grill-me` and `/plan-eng-review` first.

**Why:** Yash explicitly set this as a mandatory gate to ensure proper requirements gathering and engineering review before any implementation begins.

**How to apply:** When Yash says "build X", "add feature Y", "start project Z", or any similar implementation request — pause, run `/grill-me` to interrogate assumptions, then `/plan-eng-review` to review the plan before writing any code.
